g.text: AoiRank5Convo5 begins.

g.title: j1483232254
g.text: One thing I really admire about you is your unwavering commitment to building a better world. Where does that come from?

g.title: j3758861154
g.text: You’ve got an impressive amount of drive. What lights the fire under you?

g.title: j3709061977
g.text: oh wow thank u for saying that. umm... hmm. there’s no big defining moment that determined my life path or anything.

g.title: j1916091901
g.text: as far as I can tell, I inherited it from my parents. they were practical people, but dreamers too

g.title: j3082644319
g.text: I mean, you don’t build rockets to explore space if you're not a dreamer.

g.title: j3335029813
g.text: Wait. Your parents built rockets?

g.title: j1702753715
g.text: That’s one hell of a family business. Sounds like they set the bar high.

g.title: j2334756728
g.text: That’s not exactly a common family legacy. Did they ever talk about what inspired them?

g.title: j42785129
g.text: well, dad did. and mom knew how to.

g.title: j1713228724
g.text: ya... and when I became a soldier, they made it pretty clear it wasn't exactly the life they'd hoped to build for me.

g.title: j1108480225
g.text: not much. they weren’t big on sharing their dreams out loud. I think they believed their contributions to the world would do the talking for them.

g.title: j3584716766
g.text: dad was an aerospace engineer. mom taught space systems design at the university where they met as students.

g.title: j22857365
g.text: Wow your house was one part think tank, one part launch pad.

g.title: j1647502624
g.text: They must’ve been fascinating to talk to.

g.title: j1695454187
g.text: They sound like they were brilliant. Must’ve been incredible to grow up around that.

g.title: j1181351243
g.text: haha not really. mostly, it was just quiet.

g.title: j2574379134
g.text: yeah, I suppose so

g.title: j3314464534
g.text: a lot of our conversations were "hey, sweetie" and "hi" in passing. then they’d grab dinner on the way to their offices to work late or whatever

g.title: j3711731849
g.text: but most of our conversations were just "hey, sweetie" and "hi" as we passed each other in the kitchen. they’d grab something quick to eat and head back to their offices to work late

g.title: j2238349767
g.text: they were busy

g.title: j648177285
g.text: as long as I wasn’t getting into trouble, they didn’t worry about me much. and despite all the fire I had inside, I was really good at staying out of trouble.

g.title: j1778352328
g.text: I get that. My parents were always busy too. Running the Zariman ship was a full-time effort for everyone. Still, we always made time to sit down for meals together at least.

g.title: j2057284965
g.text: That makes sense. When work pulls you in that hard, there’s not much time left over, but I bet they thought about you constantly.

g.title: j3678428367
g.text: Can’t say I blame them. I know firsthand that space travel doesn’t leave much room for downtime. Sounds like you made their lives easier by keeping your head down.

g.title: j3754809968
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j1819041521
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j1811952594
g.text: yeah, I guess I did.

g.title: j3896946202
g.text: that's nice. I’m glad they did that.

g.title: j2262332393
g.text: maybe

g.title: j3134909228
g.text: I hope I did.

g.title: j2273916154
g.text: I realize now how important those moments are, but when I was growing up, it didn’t feel weird not to have many of them.

g.title: j506860055
g.text: actually ya, I think that's true :)

g.title: j330189443
g.text: I get why my parents were so focused on their work. in their own way, it was how they showed love. they wanted to provide for me and build technology that could help humanity have a better future

g.title: j248675736
g.text: looking back, it’s kind of beautiful

g.title: j2464642062
g.text: Maybe so, but it still doesn’t sit right with me that their daughter didn’t get more time with them. We only have so much time in this life, you know? We should spend as much of it as we can with the people we love.

g.title: j3332218587
g.text: Beautiful, sure, but practical too. They were doing something that mattered, and you don’t get much more important than that.

g.title: j1310956555
g.text: It’s a powerful kind of love, even if it’s not the kind that sits around a dinner table.

g.title: j1316308654
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j2639609404
g.text: still, I can't help but think about how we didn’t spend much time together.

g.title: j1155935438
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j1564625946
g.text: it’s the "as much of it as we can" part that’s tricky, isn’t it? hard to measure

g.title: j3031971141
g.text: if I ever see them again, I’ll make sure to make up for lost time. I know they will too.

g.title: j1550872874
g.text: right! not the kind u see in movies, but very real.

g.title: j3369924148
g.text: Fair enough. Just don’t waste time feeling bad about it now. They made their choices, and you’ve made yours. Looks like you’re doing fine with what they gave you.

g.title: j4100142575
g.text: You know, that drive of yours to make the world better... it’s deeper than you give yourself credit for. You should take more pride in it.

g.title: j3836563798
g.text: I hope you get that chance. You’ve got a heart full of hope and strength. I think they’d be proud of who you’ve become.

g.title: j206814834
g.text: I guess so

g.title: j3561934259
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j2888164891
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j2657872994
g.text: You’ve got their brains and drive, but you’ve made it your own. That’s what counts.

g.title: j3962168884
g.text: It sounds to me like you’ve grown into the kind of loving, attentive person you needed when you were younger. That’s something worth being proud of.

g.title: j3968666300
g.text: You’ve taken everything they gave you and built on it—not just with dreams and drive, but compassion too. That’s not easy to do.

g.title: j601913398
g.text: oh? how so?

g.title: j517700143
g.text: that means a lot to me. I hope so too.

g.title: j4293562950
g.text: that's... actually a really cool way to think about it.

g.title: j2244776159
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j2719702116
g.text: Just calling it like I see it.

g.title: j3474694800
g.text: Anytime.

g.title: j723862706
g.text: You deserve to hear it.

g.title: j3408738496
g.text: I’ve never thought about it like that before. that's... a really lovely way to see it. thank you.

g.text: <RETRO_EMOJI_HEART>
